result.name: Tristar Kitchen

reviews.text: I’m not impress by their soup. It is overly sweet for me. The noodle wasn’t bad, and beef was ok too, but I think the whole noodle has failed because of the soup
Visited on 10 april evening. Really bad service. 6 staffs having dinner while noodles order was still lost and outstanding. Will not visit again. There was no attempt to clean the table either .

Tried the most basic beef noodle only, with braised soup. Soup base is flavorful with depth and not overly salty. Beef is juicy and succulent, thin noodle is the usual kind. Would be good if they can put in a bit more sour veg (酸菜). Overall, quality can justify the price given its location. 

紅燒湯底有層次不算過鹹，牛腱夠腍滑，如可下多一點酸菜更好。$75一碗麵另加一，以質素來説，算OK的。

The beef noodle soup was mediocre, and the soft noodles was really too soft and disappointing. The beef chunks were too large and doesn't have too much taste. The other snacks like fried squid balls and salt chicken was good. Overall quality can't match any of the noodle places in Taipei but it is super crowded on weekend.
Great taiwanese pork rice.

result.formatted_address: 18 Sha Tin Centre St, Sha Tin, Hong Kong
result.name: New Town Plaza Phase 1

reviews.text:
The best shopping mall in Hong Kong:
1. itself + 6 more shopping malls, all inter-connected by enclosed air-conditioned walkways
2. Accessible by train, bus, minibuses, bicycles, private car (tons of parking space)
3. friendly affordable prices - not the Landmark or Pacific Place
It's easy to go around the place, convenient, but sometimes feel like the mall is kind of small.

It's the biggest mall in the region. Its been undergoing gentrification over the past few years. Local unique shops are being replaced by luxury chains. Car park is big but fills up quickly, and is expensive.
New Town Plaza Phase I is where you find the important shopping, City Super and lower level restaurant hall. There is direct access from the MTR Station and Shatin Park.
At Parkview : delicious food and good service👍

result.name: 沙田新城市廣場第一期

reviews.text: 商店按分類排列👍🏻
非常多內地客😥

成個商場嘅格局越嚟越似海港城，已經為自由行，而唔係再為沙田居民而設。
除非你真係好想買名牌，或者上食層食嘢，否則都係唔嚟好過！
小心俾自由行嘅巨型拖喼轆到隻腳， 成個商場比較行得舒服嘅係citysuper，起碼自由行唔會喺度買食材然後返屋企煮飯！

result.name: 三星台菜食堂 (沙田店)

reviews.text:
朋友推介的台灣菜食店，難得台式牛肉麵可以加蕃茄湯底，而且不是茄膏是新鮮茄肉，酸酸的感覺解了牛肉的膩，讓習慣食量小的我輕鬆清碗😂👍🏻牛肉鬆軟juicy，膠質豐富很高質！
加點了一杯黑糖珍珠奶茶，水準一般還可，不過很多冰，飲兩啖就無晒🙈

花雕雞湯只有一點花雕味，聞起來一點也不香
面吃起來很甜 很怪很難吃 質地又淋
紅燒湯底也很差 牛肉吃起來像在老火湯中煲了十世的肉乾
而且還很貴
超伏！ 一生人未食過咁難食嘅牛肉麵，成個面勁羶，係羊肉強烈嘅羶味。個紅燒湯底係多多糖+少少醋+少少辣油溝出嚟嘅。  食咗兩啖頂唔順要轉場，痴線㗎！！
I’m not impress by their soup. It is overly sweet for me. The noodle wasn’t bad, and beef was ok too, but I think the whole noodle has failed because of the soup
經過沙田..tea 一 tea,假期人太多,唯有到試三星台灣菜,來一碗🐮牛肉麵+青菜🥬😆
